---
import PrivacyDoc from '@/layouts/PrivacyDoc.astro';
import { apps } from '@/data/apps';

const app = apps.find((a) => a.id === 'codeek-map')!;
---

<PrivacyDoc app={app}>
  <p>
    Codeek Map is a mobile map tool that lets users save markers, attach photos, draw routes and
    areas, search places, and export selected data. This Privacy Policy explains what information
    the app handles, how that information is used, and what choices users have.
  </p>

  <h2>Summary</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Codeek Map does not require account registration</li>
    <li>
      Codeek Map does not include ads, analytics SDKs, or crash reporting in the current app build
    </li>
    <li>Most app data is stored locally on the user's device</li>
    <li>
      Location and photo library access are optional and used only for features the user chooses to
      use
    </li>
    <li>
      Place search sends the user's search query to the OpenStreetMap Nominatim search service so
      results can be returned
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Information We Handle</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Foreground device location for current-position and recenter features</li>
    <li>
      Photos selected by the user and copied into the app's local storage so they remain linked to
      saved marker records
    </li>
    <li>
      User-created map content such as markers, coordinates, notes, attached photo references,
      routes, waypoints, area geometry, preferences, and recent searches
    </li>
    <li>
      Search queries sent to <code>https://nominatim.openstreetmap.org/</code> when place or address
      search is used
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How Information Is Used</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Showing and recentering the map</li>
    <li>Saving user-created map items</li>
    <li>Attaching selected photos to markers</li>
    <li>Returning place search results</li>
    <li>Exporting map data to CSV or JSON files</li>
    <li>Opening the device share sheet when the user chooses to share an export</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Storage</h2>
  <p>
    Most data created in the app is stored locally on the user's device, including saved markers,
    routes, areas, preferences, and recent searches. Marker photos selected by the user are also
    stored in the app's local file storage on the device.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    Codeek Map does not sell personal information and does not share user data with advertising
    networks. Data may be shared only when search queries are sent to OpenStreetMap Nominatim or
    when export files are shared because the user explicitly chooses to share them.
  </p>

  <h2>Permissions</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <code>ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION</code> and <code>ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION</code> for current-location
      features
    </li>
    <li>
      <code>READ_MEDIA_IMAGES</code> or <code>READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE</code> to let the user pick
      photos from the device library
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Data Retention and Deletion</h2>
  <p>
    Because most app data is stored locally on the device, users can remove data by deleting saved
    items inside the app, clearing app storage through device settings, or uninstalling the app.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>Codeek Map is not intended to knowingly collect personal information from children.</p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    No method of electronic storage or transmission is completely secure, so absolute security
    cannot be guaranteed.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. The updated version should be published
    with a revised effective date.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Contact email: <code>enesk6u@gmail.com</code></p>
</PrivacyDoc>
